1
00:00:01,781 --> 00:00:03,081
The boy that Ms. Kurumi Shodo.

2
00:00:03,081 --> 00:00:06,781
"Kurumi Shodo (39)" -befriended at the beach 30 years ago,

3
00:00:06,781 --> 00:00:09,681
saved her life from a traffic accident,

4
00:00:09,681 --> 00:00:11,481
she owed her life to him.

5
00:00:12,481 --> 00:00:14,181
Kurumi says that the lottery ticket she happened to buy

6
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:15,981
was a winning ticket for 1 billion yen

7
00:00:15,981 --> 00:00:18,081
and she wants to give it to the boy who saved her.

8
00:00:18,081 --> 00:00:21,081
So, she contacted TV stations and magazines.

9
00:00:21,081 --> 00:00:23,981
The clues are her memory of the summer days

10
00:00:23,981 --> 00:00:26,281
and the large scar that the boy got

11
00:00:26,281 --> 00:00:27,681
when he saved her from the accident.

12
00:00:28,681 --> 00:00:32,281
Two men appear when she calls out for the boy.

13
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:35,081
Mr. Ryuhei Kusumoto has a large scar on his back

14
00:00:35,081 --> 00:00:36,881
and Mr. Sogo Banba has a scar on his chest.

15
00:00:36,881 --> 00:00:40,381
Both scars are large, extending in one straight line.

16
00:00:40,381 --> 00:00:43,081
In order to discern which is the real man

17
00:00:43,081 --> 00:00:45,681
we all go to visit the Shodo residence but,

18
00:00:45,681 --> 00:00:50,081
there we find the officers of the First Investigation Division

19
00:00:50,081 --> 00:00:51,481
secretly staking out in pursuit of a killer

20
00:00:51,481 --> 00:00:53,681
whose time is about to expire.

21
00:00:53,681 --> 00:00:57,581
That culprit also has a straight lined scar on his body.

22
00:00:58,581 --> 00:01:00,781
However, we also find that

23
00:01:00,781 --> 00:01:02,481
the butler at the Shodo residence,

24
00:01:02,481 --> 00:01:05,181
Mr. Taisuke Hoya has a scar on his back.

25
00:01:05,181 --> 00:01:09,081
Who on earth is the "boy of her memory"?

26
00:01:10,881 --> 00:01:12,781
Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.

27
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:15,281
Saturday nights are for mystery.

28
00:01:15,281 --> 00:01:17,281
With the deadline approaching, a first love comes to light.

29
00:01:17,281 --> 00:01:19,781
The case of the scar takes an unexpected turn!

30
00:01:19,781 --> 00:01:21,381
He sees through the one and only truth.

31
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,181
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

32
00:01:23,181 --> 00:01:25,081
No case is left unsolved with Detective Conan.

33
00:03:04,754 --> 00:03:09,754
"The Scar that Invokes the Past."

34
00:03:11,777 --> 00:03:12,877
No way.

35
00:03:12,877 --> 00:03:15,877
The butler had a scar on his back too?

36
00:03:15,877 --> 00:03:19,677
Yes. Although unlike Mr. Kusumoto and Banba's scar,

37
00:03:19,677 --> 00:03:23,377
his scar was smaller that had only about 15 cm.

38
00:03:23,377 --> 00:03:25,977
There's a chance that Hoya the butler,

39
00:03:25,977 --> 00:03:29,377
may turn out to be the murderer too.

40
00:03:29,377 --> 00:03:30,377
Why?

41
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:33,477
Isn't the scar on the murderer a big one too?

42
00:03:33,477 --> 00:03:34,977
Well, when the Superintendent slashed

43
00:03:34,977 --> 00:03:37,477
the killer and wounded him,

44
00:03:37,477 --> 00:03:40,377
he was dazed out,

45
00:03:40,377 --> 00:03:42,277
so it could be that he doesn't remember

46
00:03:42,277 --> 00:03:44,477
the accurate length of the scar.

47
00:03:44,477 --> 00:03:46,477
Besides, it seems as if that murderer

48
00:03:46,477 --> 00:03:49,377
is very cautious too.

49
00:03:50,777 --> 00:03:53,777
After that killer was slashed by the Superintendent,

50
00:03:53,777 --> 00:03:55,777
he fled by car,

51
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:58,077
but when the car was found later,

52
00:03:58,077 --> 00:04:02,277
no signs of his prints nor blood was detected at all.

53
00:04:02,277 --> 00:04:05,877
The sheet covering the driver's seat was torn off,

54
00:04:05,877 --> 00:04:08,777
so the killer probably wiped away his prints that were in the car

55
00:04:08,777 --> 00:04:11,377
after tearing off the part where his blood stains were.

56
00:04:11,377 --> 00:04:16,677
But, what makes you say that the butler may be the killer?

57
00:04:16,677 --> 00:04:18,277
If the guy is cautious,

58
00:04:18,277 --> 00:04:20,877
it's hard to believe that he would publicize himself,

59
00:04:20,877 --> 00:04:23,977
even for the sake of receiving money.

60
00:04:23,977 --> 00:04:27,177
After all, luminol reaction which usually detects

61
00:04:27,177 --> 00:04:29,477
the traces of blood even after being wiped off,

62
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:32,577
wasn't detected.

63
00:04:32,577 --> 00:04:34,977
The scars of the three men.

64
00:04:34,977 --> 00:04:38,077
There's big one on Mr. Kusumoto's back

65
00:04:38,077 --> 00:04:40,777
and Mr. Banba's chest.

66
00:04:40,777 --> 00:04:43,677
On Mr. Hoya's back there is a small scar.

67
00:04:44,677 --> 00:04:47,477
Mr. Kusumoto used to be thin when he was a child

68
00:04:47,477 --> 00:04:50,477
and, Mr. Banba used to be a bookworm.

69
00:04:50,477 --> 00:04:51,977
The boy in her memory

70
00:04:51,977 --> 00:04:53,877
was knowledgeable of the sea and fish.

71
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:56,777
His favourite drink is ginger ale.

72
00:04:56,777 --> 00:04:59,977
His favourite food are sushi and fried noodles.

73
00:04:59,977 --> 00:05:02,477
He is a very honest person.

74
00:05:02,477 --> 00:05:05,477
The nickname his classmates named him

75
00:05:05,477 --> 00:05:06,777
was Gari.

76
00:05:08,877 --> 00:05:09,877
Yes.

77
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,677
How is the investigation coming along?

78
00:05:14,677 --> 00:05:17,877
Well... Nothing definite has come up yet.

79
00:05:17,877 --> 00:05:19,277
I see.

80
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:22,077
Well, there's still more time.

81
00:05:22,077 --> 00:05:24,777
A slight meal is ready, so you can eat if you like.

82
00:05:24,777 --> 00:05:26,977
Light meal?

83
00:05:26,977 --> 00:05:30,077
Let me guess, it's...

84
00:05:30,077 --> 00:05:31,577
sushi?

85
00:05:31,577 --> 00:05:34,677
Yes, amazing how you know.

86
00:05:34,677 --> 00:05:36,677
Well, you see...

87
00:05:36,677 --> 00:05:39,077
I've got a secret to tell you.

88
00:05:40,677 --> 00:05:42,277
A little more below.

89
00:05:47,277 --> 00:05:49,177
What're they talking about?

90
00:05:50,577 --> 00:05:53,177
Will you please do so then?

91
00:05:53,177 --> 00:05:54,177
Okay.

92
00:05:55,277 --> 00:05:57,677
How surprising, though.

93
00:05:57,677 --> 00:06:01,477
I thought that you were just a short high school boy

94
00:06:01,477 --> 00:06:05,277
that still didn't go through a voice change.

95
00:06:05,277 --> 00:06:08,777
But, you're still such a little boy.

96
00:06:08,777 --> 00:06:12,777
It's as if Sherlock Holmes is pretending to be a child.

97
00:06:12,777 --> 00:06:14,377
Really?

98
00:06:14,377 --> 00:06:17,977
I can see what normal people can't.

99
00:06:19,377 --> 00:06:22,377
I'll be waiting in my room, then.

100
00:06:22,377 --> 00:06:24,777
I'll leave the rest up to you.

101
00:06:26,677 --> 00:06:27,977
Mr. Detective.

102
00:06:27,977 --> 00:06:29,777
Yes.

103
00:06:34,577 --> 00:06:36,377
Super premium sushi for sure.

104
00:06:40,677 --> 00:06:42,577
Why don't you have some too, butler?

105
00:06:42,577 --> 00:06:45,977
Kurumi said for you to eat together with us.

106
00:06:45,977 --> 00:06:47,477
Yes.

107
00:06:47,477 --> 00:06:48,777
I guess so.

108
00:06:55,677 --> 00:06:59,377
Natural stuff is good after all.

109
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,577
No, this is artificially bred fish.

110
00:07:01,577 --> 00:07:03,077
Just what're you talking about.

111
00:07:03,077 --> 00:07:05,077
This is natural stuff.

112
00:07:05,077 --> 00:07:07,577
Right, Mr. Detective. Don't you think so too?

113
00:07:07,577 --> 00:07:08,977
Oh, well...

114
00:07:08,977 --> 00:07:10,877
I really can't tell myself...

115
00:07:13,577 --> 00:07:15,277
Dad?

116
00:07:15,277 --> 00:07:18,377
Natural or artificial, you say?

117
00:07:18,377 --> 00:07:22,777
-Who cares? -Who cares?

118
00:07:22,777 --> 00:07:24,677
It's pretty important, I'd say.

119
00:07:24,677 --> 00:07:25,877
I see.

120
00:07:25,877 --> 00:07:27,977
So, is it that you want to make an impression on me

121
00:07:27,977 --> 00:07:30,077
that the boy she's looking for

122
00:07:30,077 --> 00:07:32,277
is knowledgeable about the sea and fish and likes sushi.

123
00:07:32,277 --> 00:07:35,477
Is that what you're trying to get me to see?

124
00:07:35,477 --> 00:07:36,977
Oh, no.

125
00:07:36,977 --> 00:07:38,577
Well, I guess it can't be helped

126
00:07:38,577 --> 00:07:42,277
because 1 billion yen is hanging out there.

127
00:07:42,277 --> 00:07:45,977
Talking of sushi, when that boy bought the pack of sushi,

128
00:07:45,977 --> 00:07:47,877
what did the boy do after doing so?

129
00:07:47,877 --> 00:07:49,877
The change was 100 yen more than what it was supposed to be,

130
00:07:49,877 --> 00:07:52,277
so I went to return it.

131
00:07:52,277 --> 00:07:56,177
I can't take what's not mine.

132
00:07:56,177 --> 00:07:58,277
That's strange.

133
00:07:58,277 --> 00:07:59,977
What is?

134
00:07:59,977 --> 00:08:02,277
Well... the honest boy who said that

135
00:08:02,277 --> 00:08:05,377
he can't accept what's not his

136
00:08:05,377 --> 00:08:08,577
is obviously trying to take off with 1 billion yen

137
00:08:08,577 --> 00:08:11,277
that should be going to someone else.

138
00:08:12,277 --> 00:08:15,277
What're you talking about?

139
00:08:15,277 --> 00:08:17,777
Kurumi is saying that she's going to give the 1 billion away

140
00:08:17,777 --> 00:08:21,477
as a token of her appreciation to the person who risked his own life

141
00:08:21,477 --> 00:08:24,477
to save her from a traffic accident.

142
00:08:24,477 --> 00:08:27,377
What's wrong with accepting it?

143
00:08:27,377 --> 00:08:29,777
You saw when taking a bath with me didn't you,

144
00:08:29,777 --> 00:08:32,177
the scar from the accident back then.

145
00:08:32,177 --> 00:08:35,277
No, the scar on my back

146
00:08:35,277 --> 00:08:38,077
is indeed the scar I got during the accident.

147
00:08:38,077 --> 00:08:43,077
True, you had a large scar about 30 cm long,

148
00:08:43,077 --> 00:08:47,677
but that is again exactly what made me doubt you.

149
00:08:48,677 --> 00:08:52,477
Kurumi answered the interview on TV, didn't she?

150
00:08:52,477 --> 00:08:55,677
That the scar extended from one end to the other.

151
00:08:55,677 --> 00:08:57,777
She doesn't remember if the scar was on the chest or back,

152
00:08:57,777 --> 00:09:00,077
but it was a big scar.

153
00:09:00,077 --> 00:09:01,377
She said she was sure of that.

154
00:09:01,377 --> 00:09:04,977
Then, how old were you then?

155
00:09:04,977 --> 00:09:08,177
Around 2nd or 3rd grade of elementary school.

156
00:09:08,177 --> 00:09:11,577
Really? If the boy was in 2nd or 3rd grade of elementary,

157
00:09:11,577 --> 00:09:15,777
a scar reaching from side to side would be about 15 cm...

158
00:09:15,777 --> 00:09:17,977
Well. I guess...

159
00:09:17,977 --> 00:09:20,977
When I first got the scar, it was about that long, but...

160
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:23,777
As I got older and my body got bigger,

161
00:09:23,777 --> 00:09:26,077
my scar got bigger too.

162
00:09:27,077 --> 00:09:29,477
Don't you know?

163
00:09:29,477 --> 00:09:33,077
Scars don't get larger even if a person grows up.

164
00:09:33,077 --> 00:09:34,977
-What? -What?

165
00:09:34,977 --> 00:09:37,777
If you get a scar that's 15 cm,

166
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:40,377
the scar stays the same size until you die.

167
00:09:40,377 --> 00:09:43,977
Well, I was pretty big for my age.

168
00:09:43,977 --> 00:09:45,277
Me too.

169
00:09:45,277 --> 00:09:47,177
Mr. Kusumoto.

170
00:09:47,177 --> 00:09:51,777
Didn't you say that you were very thin when you were a child?

171
00:09:51,777 --> 00:09:54,177
I did...

172
00:09:54,177 --> 00:09:56,977
He probably said he was skinny

173
00:09:56,977 --> 00:09:58,577
after hearing that the boy she's looking for

174
00:09:58,577 --> 00:10:00,677
was nicknamed Gari.

175
00:10:00,677 --> 00:10:03,077
He probably mistook it for "gari-gari" which means skinny.

176
00:10:03,077 --> 00:10:05,177
He was actually nicknamed Gari

177
00:10:05,177 --> 00:10:08,577
because he was a bookworm.

178
00:10:08,577 --> 00:10:11,177
Gari because he was a bookworm?

179
00:10:11,177 --> 00:10:12,577
Do you know?

180
00:10:12,577 --> 00:10:17,577
When that boy ate fried noodles at the beach house,

181
00:10:17,577 --> 00:10:20,777
he put a lot of red ginger on it.

182
00:10:20,777 --> 00:10:22,477
What's that about?

183
00:10:22,477 --> 00:10:24,877
I don't know about it.

184
00:10:24,877 --> 00:10:27,477
It's only natural that you don't know about it.

185
00:10:27,477 --> 00:10:29,777
I heard about it for the first time today too.

186
00:10:29,777 --> 00:10:31,877
It's a trump card.

187
00:10:32,877 --> 00:10:35,377
Don't you understand yet?

188
00:10:35,377 --> 00:10:39,077
The boy liked ginger ale,

189
00:10:39,077 --> 00:10:41,877
bought sushi packs often

190
00:10:41,877 --> 00:10:44,977
and used to put a lot of red ginger on his fried noodles.

191
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:49,277
I see. That boy liked ginger.

192
00:10:49,277 --> 00:10:51,977
There's ginger in ginger ale

193
00:10:51,977 --> 00:10:53,977
and the ginger that comes with sushi

194
00:10:53,977 --> 00:10:57,177
is ginger marinated in sugar and vinegar.

195
00:10:57,177 --> 00:10:58,777
Which means that the reason

196
00:10:58,777 --> 00:10:59,977
the boy got the nickname Gari was because...

197
00:10:59,977 --> 00:11:01,377
Yes, that's right.

198
00:11:01,377 --> 00:11:05,377
He was probably called Gari because he loved ginger.

199
00:11:05,377 --> 00:11:07,177
That's right, isn't it?

200
00:11:07,177 --> 00:11:09,677
You didn't even bother to eat the sushi

201
00:11:09,677 --> 00:11:11,977
but went right for the ginger and ate it all up,

202
00:11:11,977 --> 00:11:14,477
didn't you, Mr. Hoya?

203
00:11:16,377 --> 00:11:17,377
No way.

204
00:11:17,377 --> 00:11:19,477
You mean the real guy was here?

205
00:11:19,477 --> 00:11:24,477
Yes. He has a scar about 15 cm on his back too.

206
00:11:24,477 --> 00:11:26,977
So, there's probably no mistake about it.

207
00:11:26,977 --> 00:11:29,477
Then, why doesn't he come right out and say so?

208
00:11:29,477 --> 00:11:31,977
He could get a billion yen.

209
00:11:33,077 --> 00:11:36,277
I can't accept that money.

210
00:11:36,277 --> 00:11:40,677
Because if I didn't tell her to stay,

211
00:11:40,677 --> 00:11:44,677
she may have not gotten into the accident.

212
00:11:44,677 --> 00:11:46,877
That's why I decided to watch over her

213
00:11:46,877 --> 00:11:48,177
without revealing my identity.

214
00:11:48,177 --> 00:11:49,977
But, it seems that you couldn't do so

215
00:11:49,977 --> 00:11:52,377
without revealing your true identity.

216
00:11:52,377 --> 00:11:54,177
Do you know why?

217
00:11:54,177 --> 00:11:56,377
Kurumi who knew that you're the type

218
00:11:56,377 --> 00:11:59,477
that would never accept what is not yours,

219
00:11:59,477 --> 00:12:02,377
went on air and publicized

220
00:12:02,377 --> 00:12:04,477
that she wanted to give you the billion yen?

221
00:12:05,677 --> 00:12:07,677
It's because she wanted you,

222
00:12:07,677 --> 00:12:10,577
who was right beside her to come out on your own.

223
00:12:10,577 --> 00:12:12,377
And to tell you to not publicize something like that

224
00:12:12,377 --> 00:12:15,477
because it may bring about imposters.

225
00:12:16,877 --> 00:12:19,577
Then... Kurumi knew, after all.

226
00:12:19,577 --> 00:12:21,877
Yes, she was aware

227
00:12:21,877 --> 00:12:26,877
that Mr. Hoya was the boy she had known back then.

228
00:12:26,877 --> 00:12:29,077
That's why she made him wash my back in the bath tub

229
00:12:29,077 --> 00:12:31,577
where the air conditioner was out of order.

230
00:12:31,577 --> 00:12:35,277
She didn't say anything about the red ginger till today.

231
00:12:35,277 --> 00:12:37,677
She served sushi as a late-night meal.

232
00:12:37,677 --> 00:12:40,877
She did all this to drop hints at me.

233
00:12:40,877 --> 00:12:44,077
So, what now, Mr. Hoya?

234
00:12:44,077 --> 00:12:47,177
Kurumi is waiting in her room.

235
00:12:49,677 --> 00:12:52,477
But... Well...

236
00:12:52,477 --> 00:12:54,177
I...

237
00:12:54,177 --> 00:12:56,177
You'll be fine.

238
00:12:56,177 --> 00:12:59,677
I'll go tell the lady for you in your place.

239
00:13:00,777 --> 00:13:04,077
If you like, shall I go tell her for you?

240
00:13:04,077 --> 00:13:06,277
I really don't want people who are just after the money

241
00:13:06,277 --> 00:13:08,177
lying and saying that they are the ones

242
00:13:08,177 --> 00:13:09,577
that she is looking for besides.

243
00:13:11,577 --> 00:13:15,777
Okay. I'll go tell her myself.

244
00:13:24,277 --> 00:13:26,277
He seems to have been urged to do what he has to do.

245
00:13:26,277 --> 00:13:27,777
Yes.

246
00:13:27,777 --> 00:13:33,977
Jeepers. I'd like to tell the truth if I could, but can't.

247
00:13:33,977 --> 00:13:35,677
Just who are talking about?

248
00:13:38,177 --> 00:13:39,977
Kamen Yaiba.

249
00:13:39,977 --> 00:13:42,377
He can't afford to have people know his true identity.

250
00:13:43,477 --> 00:13:45,477
Then, I guess I'll be going.

251
00:13:45,477 --> 00:13:47,277
Bye.

252
00:13:49,677 --> 00:13:52,377
Hold it, will you?

253
00:13:52,377 --> 00:13:53,977
Police?

254
00:13:53,977 --> 00:13:56,177
I... I was just joking.

255
00:13:56,177 --> 00:13:57,977
I had a scar on my chest

256
00:13:57,977 --> 00:13:59,577
that I got when I got hurt surfing, so...

257
00:13:59,577 --> 00:14:02,277
No, the one that we want

258
00:14:02,277 --> 00:14:04,977
is the guy with the large scar on his back.

259
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:06,277
You. That is.

260
00:14:07,377 --> 00:14:09,277
Because after all,

261
00:14:09,277 --> 00:14:12,977
that wound is the straight-line scar

262
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:16,877
what Superintendent Matsumoto left on the serial killer 20 years ago

263
00:14:16,877 --> 00:14:19,477
when he cornered the culprit.

264
00:14:19,477 --> 00:14:20,677
What?

