00:14:20,677 --> 00:14:25,077
Back then, I didn't know if the scar was on the chest or the back but...

266
00:14:25,077 --> 00:14:27,577
it cleared after I got the mail from Mouri.

267
00:14:27,577 --> 00:14:29,777
Mail?

268
00:14:29,777 --> 00:14:30,977
Oh no.

269
00:14:30,977 --> 00:14:33,477
I've got to return Pop's cell phone to him.

270
00:14:33,477 --> 00:14:36,077
Normally, when people are wounded,

271
00:14:36,077 --> 00:14:39,177
they reflexively cover that area with their hands.

272
00:14:39,177 --> 00:14:42,877
So, the fact that there was no luminol reaction detected

273
00:14:42,877 --> 00:14:45,677
on the steering wheel of the car that was abandoned

274
00:14:45,677 --> 00:14:49,477
was because the killer couldn't reach his wound.

275
00:14:49,477 --> 00:14:52,277
In other words, he was wounded on his back.

276
00:14:53,277 --> 00:14:55,977
Tearing away the cover of the driver's seat

277
00:14:55,977 --> 00:15:00,077
in order to hide the blood stains inside the car gave you away.

278
00:15:00,077 --> 00:15:03,477
Oh, no... That's not it.

279
00:15:03,477 --> 00:15:06,677
The scar on the back of a man I met before looked cool,

280
00:15:06,677 --> 00:15:08,677
so I copied him and scarred my back.

281
00:15:08,677 --> 00:15:11,277
You'd better cut out your wisecracks.

282
00:15:11,277 --> 00:15:13,777
It's true, please believe me.

283
00:15:13,777 --> 00:15:17,377
Was that man whistling?

284
00:15:17,377 --> 00:15:18,877
How about it?

285
00:15:18,877 --> 00:15:20,777
Yes.

286
00:15:20,777 --> 00:15:22,277
If I remember correctly,

287
00:15:22,277 --> 00:15:25,177
it was a tune that was popular about 20 years ago.

288
00:15:25,177 --> 00:15:27,177
You're not lying, are you?

289
00:15:27,177 --> 00:15:28,377
No.

290
00:15:28,377 --> 00:15:30,877
Superintendent.

291
00:15:30,877 --> 00:15:33,477
Popular 20 years ago.

292
00:15:33,477 --> 00:15:36,377
That's the tune of the serial killer.

293
00:15:43,899 --> 00:15:47,099
Ryuhei Kusumoto, age 42.

294
00:15:47,099 --> 00:15:49,499
Around the time the incident occurred 15 years ago,

295
00:15:49,499 --> 00:15:52,399
he seems to have been abroad home-staying.

296
00:15:52,399 --> 00:15:54,399
This has been confirmed,

297
00:15:54,399 --> 00:15:56,999
so I guess he could be cleared from the list of suspects.

298
00:15:56,999 --> 00:15:58,099
I see.

299
00:15:59,099 --> 00:16:01,799
He seems to have met the man with the scar on his back at a sauna

300
00:16:01,799 --> 00:16:05,699
just before he left to go abroad to home-stay.

301
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:07,799
He seems to have had a towel over his head,

302
00:16:07,799 --> 00:16:09,899
so didn't see the face of the man.

303
00:16:10,899 --> 00:16:12,099
The man seems to have laughed and said,

304
00:16:12,099 --> 00:16:14,499
"This scar was made on my back 5 years ago

305
00:16:14,499 --> 00:16:16,099
by the police and is a crest of courage.

306
00:16:16,099 --> 00:16:19,099
You want to have one like this too?"

307
00:16:19,099 --> 00:16:20,799
Is anyone at that sauna?

308
00:16:20,799 --> 00:16:24,499
Officer Sato and Takagi are staking out there right now.

309
00:16:24,499 --> 00:16:27,499
Tell them to stay on their guard.

310
00:16:27,499 --> 00:16:28,799
Yes, sir.

311
00:16:28,799 --> 00:16:32,399
He's a vicious killer who killed a total of 3 people,

312
00:16:32,399 --> 00:16:35,899
2 people 20 years ago and 1 person 15 years ago.

313
00:16:37,099 --> 00:16:39,299
No, there's one more.

314
00:16:39,299 --> 00:16:40,999
Did you forget?

315
00:16:41,999 --> 00:16:44,399
I'd never forget

316
00:16:44,399 --> 00:16:46,499
about Superintendent Morimura who died on duty

317
00:16:46,499 --> 00:16:48,999
because of that incident.

318
00:16:48,999 --> 00:16:52,099
After all, he's the one who taught me all I need to know

319
00:16:52,099 --> 00:16:53,899
about being a police detective.

320
00:17:00,399 --> 00:17:03,599
Superintendent Morimura.

321
00:17:03,599 --> 00:17:05,199
After you died on duty,

322
00:17:05,199 --> 00:17:07,599
you were specially promoted 2 ranks,

323
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:10,099
and I've finally caught up to your rank now.

324
00:17:10,099 --> 00:17:12,099
But, I still don't understand

325
00:17:12,099 --> 00:17:14,899
the meaning of the words you said back then.

326
00:17:16,099 --> 00:17:19,899
Matsumoto, there's some meaning

327
00:17:19,899 --> 00:17:23,899
behind the tune that... that guy is whistling.

328
00:17:23,899 --> 00:17:26,599
I'm dead sure... there's something.

329
00:17:27,699 --> 00:17:32,299
What on earth could there be, Morimura?

330
00:17:33,299 --> 00:17:35,899
So there was nothing after all.

331
00:17:35,899 --> 00:17:37,099
Nothing at all.

332
00:17:37,099 --> 00:17:39,099
Well, it can't be helped.

333
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:41,499
It's an incident that happened 15 years ago.

334
00:17:41,499 --> 00:17:42,699
I guess so.

335
00:17:42,699 --> 00:17:44,699
The building itself seems to have been renovated,

336
00:17:44,699 --> 00:17:47,699
and the people who come here seem to have changed too.

337
00:17:47,699 --> 00:17:48,799
Come to think of it,

338
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:50,799
the sauna at 5-chome seems to have been greatly renovated

339
00:17:50,799 --> 00:17:52,399
and has a good reputation.

340
00:17:52,399 --> 00:17:54,399
That's right.

341
00:17:54,399 --> 00:17:57,899
Why don't you invite Officer Chiba and go there with him?

342
00:17:57,899 --> 00:18:00,099
I'll go, alone.

343
00:18:01,199 --> 00:18:03,399
Did you ask me to come with you?

344
00:18:03,399 --> 00:18:05,799
Of course!

345
00:18:05,799 --> 00:18:07,799
Then, why don't we do this?

346
00:18:07,799 --> 00:18:09,199
If we get to arrest this serial killer

347
00:18:09,199 --> 00:18:11,199
before the expiration date,

348
00:18:11,199 --> 00:18:13,799
let's go to a hot spring together.

349
00:18:13,799 --> 00:18:15,999
But, we've only got three more days to go.

350
00:18:15,999 --> 00:18:18,399
Take me to a hot spring.

351
00:18:18,399 --> 00:18:19,599
You know what...

352
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,199
I wonder, is it okay?

353
00:18:22,199 --> 00:18:25,599
For officers to be acting lovey-dovey on duty.

354
00:18:25,599 --> 00:18:28,599
Oh, no. We're not acting lovey-dovey.

355
00:18:28,599 --> 00:18:30,799
We're questioning the people around here...

356
00:18:31,799 --> 00:18:34,499
Don't tell the children what you don't have to.

357
00:18:34,499 --> 00:18:36,099
I know.

358
00:18:36,099 --> 00:18:39,699
If I put together the details of the incident that was aired on TV

359
00:18:39,699 --> 00:18:42,699
and what Superintendent Matsumoto said,

360
00:18:42,699 --> 00:18:45,399
the first incident happened 20 years ago.

361
00:18:45,399 --> 00:18:48,299
The victim was a doctor, aged 50,

362
00:18:48,299 --> 00:18:50,399
called Mr. Tsuguharu Bokawa.

363
00:18:50,399 --> 00:18:54,299
The murder weapon was the Japanese sword that he owned.

364
00:18:54,299 --> 00:18:56,499
Two days later,

365
00:18:56,499 --> 00:18:58,099
the professor of the science and technology department

366
00:18:58,099 --> 00:19:01,499
of Tohto University, Mr. Atsunori Mugita, age 42,

367
00:19:01,499 --> 00:19:03,699
was killed with the same Japanese sword.

368
00:19:03,699 --> 00:19:06,499
When the officer who was asking questions in the area

369
00:19:06,499 --> 00:19:09,499
about a car that was seen often and thought to be suspicious,

370
00:19:09,499 --> 00:19:10,999
it fled and ran over the officer.

371
00:19:10,999 --> 00:19:14,499
The officer as a result died on duty.

372
00:19:14,499 --> 00:19:17,399
Superintendent Matsumoto who cornered the car

373
00:19:17,399 --> 00:19:19,199
was attacked by the culprit

374
00:19:19,199 --> 00:19:20,999
and was hurt in the left eye,

375
00:19:20,999 --> 00:19:24,299
but despite being hurt grabbed the sword from the culprit

376
00:19:24,299 --> 00:19:27,699
and slashed him leaving a straight-lined wound on his back.

377
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:29,799
And, five years later,

378
00:19:29,799 --> 00:19:32,199
Lawyer Susumu Nabei, age 34,

379
00:19:32,199 --> 00:19:35,299
was killed at his residence with a knife that was in his house.

380
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:38,599
First the victims were knocked out by a stun gun,

381
00:19:38,599 --> 00:19:42,899
then viciously slashed using a Japanese sword or a knife.

382
00:19:42,899 --> 00:19:44,499
In all three incidents

383
00:19:44,499 --> 00:19:46,799
there were no signs of the door being forced open,

384
00:19:46,799 --> 00:19:48,599
so investigation was carried out under the presumption

385
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:50,199
that it was committed by an acquaintance.

386
00:19:50,199 --> 00:19:51,999
No common points what so ever were found among the three victims,

387
00:19:51,999 --> 00:19:54,899
and the investigation was coming to a dead end.

388
00:19:54,899 --> 00:19:56,399
Is that correct?

389
00:19:56,399 --> 00:19:57,899
Yes.

390
00:19:57,899 --> 00:20:00,199
But, I don't understand.

391
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:02,899
The first and second victims were killed with the same weapon

392
00:20:02,899 --> 00:20:05,599
so it was probably the same killer.

393
00:20:05,599 --> 00:20:06,899
Right.

394
00:20:06,899 --> 00:20:09,699
A knife was used to commit the murder five years later.

395
00:20:09,699 --> 00:20:12,299
How did you figure out it was the same culprit?

396
00:20:12,299 --> 00:20:13,599
Well, that's...

397
00:20:13,599 --> 00:20:14,799
That was because the letter

398
00:20:14,799 --> 00:20:18,199
-that was on the victim's body was... -Hey, Officer Sato.

399
00:20:18,199 --> 00:20:21,399
You're telling her about it too.

400
00:20:21,399 --> 00:20:22,499
I'm sorry.

401
00:20:22,499 --> 00:20:24,399
I can't seem to stop myself when they ask me questions.

402
00:20:24,399 --> 00:20:27,899
-So, there are only three more days to go... -They're still broadcasting.

403
00:20:27,899 --> 00:20:30,199
-Do you think the police... -that incident now.

404
00:20:30,199 --> 00:20:32,299
will be able to arrest the culprit, Mr. Hiramune?

405
00:20:32,299 --> 00:20:36,799
Well, I think it's impossible judging from the present circumstance.

406
00:20:36,799 --> 00:20:38,299
"Doji Hiramune (41)" -The culprit probably

407
00:20:38,299 --> 00:20:39,999
has all the curtains closed,

408
00:20:39,999 --> 00:20:41,399
and has all the telephone jacks pulled out

409
00:20:41,399 --> 00:20:43,299
to keep out of contact from everything on the outside.

410
00:20:43,299 --> 00:20:45,599
He's probably shivering in bed waiting

411
00:20:45,599 --> 00:20:48,599
for the three days to go by.

412
00:20:48,599 --> 00:20:51,699
He's probably trying with all his might

413
00:20:51,699 --> 00:20:54,099
to keep a low profile and pass the time away.

414
00:20:54,099 --> 00:20:57,499
If this isn't true, come to here to me.

415
00:20:58,499 --> 00:21:01,199
That is, if you want to waste all the effort

416
00:21:01,199 --> 00:21:03,899
